triageCases.transcript: Hello, I'm calling because my right ear has been really painful for two days now. Yesterday I noticed some yellowish fluid coming out of it, and I have a fever. I had a bad cold last week.
triageCases.aiSummary: Patient reports severe ear pain for 48 hours, discharge from right ear, fever of 101.5°F. Recent upper respiratory infection. Possible acute otitis media with perforation. Requires urgent evaluation.

triageCases.transcript: I've had this sinus pressure for about three weeks now. My nose is constantly stuffed and I have thick green mucus. My forehead and cheeks hurt, especially when I bend over. This has happened before.
triageCases.aiSummary: Patient experiencing facial pressure, thick nasal discharge, and headaches for 3 weeks. No fever. Previous episodes treated with antibiotics. Likely chronic sinusitis with post-nasal drip. Suggests follow-up within 3-5 days.
triageCases.resolutionReason: Appointment scheduled for November 20, 2024. Patient contacted and confirmed. Prescribed antibiotics pending examination.
triageCases.clinicianSummary: Chronic sinusitis case. Patient has history of similar episodes. Scheduled for in-office examination and possible CT scan.

triageCases.transcript: My left ear has felt plugged up for a couple weeks now. I can't hear as well out of it. No pain or anything, it just feels full and muffled. I think it might be wax buildup.
triageCases.aiSummary: Patient reports decreased hearing in left ear, feels 'full'. No pain or discharge. Symptoms gradual over 2 weeks. Mild cerumen impaction suspected. Routine appointment appropriate.
triageCases.resolutionReason: Routine appointment scheduled for November 25, 2024. Ear wax removal anticipated. Patient provided pre-visit instructions for ear drops.
triageCases.clinicianSummary: Standard cerumen impaction. Scheduled for removal procedure.

triageCases.transcript: I can barely swallow, the pain is so bad. My throat is really swollen on one side and I have a high fever. It hurts to talk and I'm drooling because I can't swallow my saliva properly.
triageCases.aiSummary: Severe throat pain with difficulty swallowing and speaking. Fever 103°F. Unilateral swelling. Muffled voice noted. Possible peritonsillar abscess. Requires immediate evaluation - potential emergency.
triageCases.resolutionReason: Emergency same-day appointment provided. Patient evaluated and confirmed peritonsillar abscess. Referred to hospital for I&D procedure.
triageCases.clinicianSummary: Confirmed peritonsillar abscess on examination. Patient sent to ER for incision and drainage. Prescribed antibiotics and pain management.

triageCases.transcript: I've lost my voice almost completely. It started five days ago and it's not getting better. I had a slight fever at first but that's gone now. I can barely speak above a whisper.
triageCases.aiSummary: Patient with hoarseness for 5 days, worse in mornings. Low-grade fever initially, now resolved. No respiratory distress. Acute laryngitis, possibly viral etiology. Suggest follow-up if not improved in 7-10 days.

triageCases.transcript: I've been sneezing constantly for two weeks. My nose is running clear and my eyes are so itchy. This happens to me every fall. I've been taking over-the-counter allergy medicine but it's not helping much.
triageCases.aiSummary: Recurrent sneezing, clear nasal discharge, and itchy eyes for 2 weeks. No fever or colored discharge. History of seasonal allergies. Seasonal allergic rhinitis. Routine consultation appropriate.

triageCases.transcript: I woke up this morning and couldn't hear anything out of my right ear. It's completely gone, and there's a ringing sound. I didn't hit my head or anything. I'm really scared.
triageCases.aiSummary: Patient reports sudden complete hearing loss in right ear upon waking, with tinnitus. No trauma or infection symptoms. Sudden sensorineural hearing loss suspected. Requires urgent evaluation within 24-48 hours for best prognosis.
triageCases.resolutionReason: Urgent same-day appointment provided. Patient evaluated with audiometry. Started on high-dose corticosteroid treatment immediately.
triageCases.clinicianSummary: Sudden SNHL confirmed. Immediate steroid treatment initiated. Follow-up audiogram scheduled for 1 week. MRI ordered to rule out acoustic neuroma.

triageCases.transcript: I've had several nosebleeds this week, maybe three or four times. They last about ten to fifteen minutes before stopping. I take blood pressure medicine. The bleeding is from my right nostril mostly.
triageCases.aiSummary: Frequent nosebleeds over past week, 3-4 episodes lasting 10-15 minutes each. Patient on blood pressure medication. No trauma. Recurrent epistaxis, possible hypertension-related. Requires evaluation and possible cauterization.

triageCases.transcript: Whenever I turn my head quickly or roll over in bed, the room spins for about thirty seconds. It's been happening for a few days now. My hearing is fine and I don't have any ear pain.
triageCases.aiSummary: Dizzy spells triggered by head movements, especially rolling over in bed. Episodes last seconds to minutes. No hearing loss or tinnitus. Benign paroxysmal positional vertigo (BPPV) suspected. Canalith repositioning may be beneficial.
triageCases.resolutionReason: Appointment scheduled for November 22, 2024. Epley maneuver planned. Patient provided with pre-visit instructions.
triageCases.clinicianSummary: Classic BPPV presentation. Scheduled for Dix-Hallpike test and Epley maneuver.

triageCases.transcript: My four-year-old has had this awful smell coming from his nose for three days now. There's yellow discharge but only from the left nostril. He says he didn't put anything up there, but I'm not sure.
triageCases.aiSummary: Parent reports child (age 4) has foul-smelling unilateral nasal discharge for 3 days. Child denied inserting object. Suspected nasal foreign body (pediatric). Requires visualization and possible removal.
